# encoding: utf-8
=begin

  Highlight Manager - color highlights for GemStone IV front ends

  Highlight Manager helps you keep player-name and custom text highlights in
  one place.

  In simple terms, it can:
    - learn player race and profession from WHO
    - remember names between runs
    - color names by profession, race, race + profession, or manual label
    - add labels like Friend, Family, Enemy, Self, or your own labels
    - import existing Wrayth/StormFront/Warlock highlight XML
    - manage custom text/phrase highlights
    - write highlight-manager-importme.xml for your front end to import
    - copy highlights into Wrayth/StormFront character XML files after making
      backups and asking you to confirm the paths
    - look up saved name data from the command line
    - save private notes on names so lookup can remind you why someone is highlighted

  Front-end support:
    - Wrayth/StormFront on Windows: import the generated XML in Settings -> Import.
    - Warlock on Windows or Mac: import Highlight Manager's generated XML in
      Warlock Settings. Global import is usually easiest. Warlock does not need
      the copy tool.
    - Wizard and Avalon: scan and lookup only. Highlight import/export/setup
      features are disabled.

  Privacy note:
    Warlock settings XML can contain saved login/private data.
    Highlight Manager can read Warlock XML when importing existing highlights,
    but it only reads highlight sections and does not save passwords or other
    private settings. Keep full Warlock settings XML local. Do not post or
    share it.

  Helpful commands:
    ;highlight-manager
        Scan WHO and rewrite the import file.
    ;highlight-manager setup
        Open the setup window.
    ;highlight-manager help
        Show the full command list.
    ;highlight-manager version
        Show the version and build.
    ;highlight-manager changelog
        Show recent release notes.

       author: Mystienne
  contributor: Peggyanne, Eternil
         game: gs
      version: 1.1.24
        build: 20260523.5
         tags: highlights, names, professions, races, colors, tags, customization, frontend
     required: Lich >= 5.11.0
        email: Mystienne@mystienne.com
      discord: Mystienne

=end

